Package: ESPRESSO.G
Type: Package
Title: Power Analysis and Sample Size Calculation for a model with a
    main effect genetic variant
Version: 1.0
Date: 2013-04-01
Author: Amadou Gaye
Maintainer: Amadou Gaye <ag239@le.ac.uk>
Description: The package allows for the Estimation of Sample-size and Power by
    Exploring Simulated Study Outcomes for a main effect model where the
    covariate is biallelic SNP. It supports simulation-based power
    calculation for stand-alone case-control studies and for case-control
    analyses nested in cohort studies, that take account of realistic
    assessment error.
Depends:
    MASS
License: GPL-2
LazyLoad: yes
Collate:
    'get.critical.results.G.R'
    'get.observed.data.G.R'
    'get.obs.geno.R'
    'get.obs.pheno.R'
    'glm.analysis.G.R'
    'misclassify.R'
    'power.calc.R'
    'run.espresso.G.R'
    'samplsize.calc.R'
    'sim.CC.data.G.R'
    'sim.geno.data.R'
    'sim.pheno.bin.G.R'
    'sim.pheno.qtl.G.R'
    'sim.QTL.data.G.R'
    'sim.subject.data.R'
